Raid anon here. I know I barely did anything for the thread but I wanted to make this announcement for anyone who does care about my work. I don't feel right in continuing it anymore. Not due to the dubject of the stories, no no no not at all. I wanted to create a villian with minor sympathies and I think with Mous's help in the end I will. I feel that I've been robbing Mous of his time when he is also already pressed for time as of late. Combine that with how deeply he edits and rewrites my works and I honestly feel like I'm taking too much without something in return for him. Combine that with not feeling as if the hunts have a reason outside of a strange malice I eanted to try to show off and I just don't think that HMoFA is entirely right for me. I really do enjoy the stories, art, and shitposts here but I just feel off when I try to write about a villainous protagonist that is definitely rubbing some people in thread the wrong way. So as of today I'm going to step away from the threads and try to think of a better idea of sorts to write as well as admittedly trying to figure out and copy Mous's style with his permission. I probably won't be back this year at all, and after today I may not come back if we're being honest.

>What does this mean for your stories directly?
>Will the cyoa still happen?
Mous will finish my stories when he has time. Blok's monster hunter commission was a gift to Mous so I could feel better about myself for giving him my final drafts to finish in his spare time. The CYOA wi still happen and I'll be backseating dice rolls and the occasional voting option or random happening. Mousguy will be in control of "the raider" and his eventual meeting with certain key members of the BHA in the future as of today. I'm sorry if you wanted a story from me or something, but I can answer questions if anyone has them or some shit I guess.
